snippet: Opponents of President Viktor F. Yanukovich on Tuesday unsuccessfully demanded his resignation as protesters continued a siege of government buildings.
abstract: Ukrainian Parliament defeats measure calling for the resignation of Prime Min Mykola Azarov and his government, refusing to grant a central demand of protesters who have laid siege to public buildings and occupied a landmark plaza in Kiev; demonstrators and allied political opposition leaders say they will not relent until they succeed in removing government, including Pres Viktor F Yanukovich.

byline.original: By DAVID M. HERSZENHORN and ANDREW E. KRAMER
byline.contributor: Michael R. Gordon contributed reporting from Brussels, and Oksana Lyachynska from Kiev.

lead_paragraph: Opponents of President Viktor F. Yanukovich on Tuesday unsuccessfully demanded his resignation as protesters continued a siege of government buildings.

headline.main: Ukraine Protests Persist as Bid to Oust Government Fails
headline.print_headline: Ukraine Protests Persist as Bid to Oust Government Fails
